      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MY IRISH (2) has a strong record here with five wins and four placings from 10 starts. Hit the frame latest (25.00) when third at this track in a Grade 5. Makes strong appeal on best. COLD COLD NIGHT (1) made light work of the tricky draw with a fast early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing second (29.78) at Wentworth Park over 520m. Can feature again. FROM THE DISCO (3) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (24.84) at this track behind Ava's Milo in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Has won four of eight starts from this draw. Winning chance. SHORTY (6) must be respected despite an unplaced effort here most recently.",
